Convicted racist Vicki Momberg's leave to appeal both her conviction and sentencing was dismissed by the Randburg Magistrate's Court on Wednesday Momberg (49)was sentenced to three years’ imprisonment, with one year suspended, by the same court last month. READ MORE: Vicki Momberg back in dock to apply for leave to appeal In June 2017, the Equality Court awarded damages of R100 000 to Constable Clement Mkhondo after he was verbally assaulted by Momberg.